abstract_ssm: The Sam Wallach Papers include materials from Sam Wallach (1909-2001) and Rose Russell (1899-1965) New York teachers who were active in the Teachers' Union in the 1940s and 1950s.  Wallach was fired by the New York City Board of Education in 1951 for refusal to cooperate with various bodies investigating Communism.
